# Anxiety
My brain is in the process of hypersensitivity due to GABA instability and deregulation. It is going to take me a few months to be able to go outside and go gym and other things I love. But for the time being I can only focus on my academics, coding, and math. 
Thus there are a few new side projects I will be busy with.

1. Apply Fourier analysis to signal obfuscation ideas.
2. Model anxiety as a dynamical system (nonlinear differential equations).
3. Study information theory alongside cybersecurity.
4. Learn category theory basics and connect to programming abstractions.

# Modeling anxiety as a dynamical system (nonlinear differential equation)
Since I have never modeled an event as a Differntial Equation(DE) from scratch (I am usually just given DEs or its applications to solve), I think it will be a good starting point to first identify the variables that influence the DE.
